      "comment_id" : 12150084,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Well, whether or not the machines themselves are still in use, you have to assume there are still documents out there that were <i>written</i> on pre-OSX Macs.  I know it&#39;s tempting to shorten <code>(?:\\r?\\n|\\r)</code> to <code>(?:\\r?n)</code>, but no, I don&#39;t think it&#39;s safe.  I prefer <code>(?:\\r\\n|[\\r\\n])</code> anyway; I know it&#39;s more characters, but it looks neater. :D  And if you don&#39;t care <i>how many</i> line separators you consume, <code>[\\r\\n]+</code> works just fine."
